{\bf ABSTRACT}\\[.0015in]
\end{center}
We study the four-point correlator of ${\textstyle \frac{1}{2}}$-BPS operators of weight 4 in
${\cal N}=4$ SYM, which are dual to massive KK modes in AdS${}_5$ supergravity.
General field-theoretic arguments lead to a partially non-renormalized form of the amplitude that depends on two {\it a priori} independent functions of the conformal cross-ratios. We explicitly compute the amplitude in the large $N$ limit at one loop (order $g^2$) and in AdS${}_5$ supergravity. \\
Surprisingly, the one-loop result shows that the two functions determining the amplitude {\it coincide} while in the supergravity regime they are  {\it distinctly different}. We discuss the possible implications of this perturbative degeneracy for the AdS/CFT correspondence.

